# Keep the build context minimal and never stream the secret (.env with
# GRAFANA_ADMIN_PASSWORD) to the Docker daemon (WX-274, WX-278).  Ignore
# everything, then allow only what the Dockerfiles actually COPY.  This
# guarantees .env can never be baked into an image layer even if a COPY is
# later broadened by mistake.  The Dockerfiles themselves are read as build
# instructions regardless of this file, so they need no allow-entry.
#
# .env lives at the context ROOT (observability/.env), not under grafana/, and
# stays excluded by `*`.  We allow-list ONLY the two grafana/ subtrees that
# grafana.Dockerfile actually COPYs -- provisioning + dashboards -- so the
# "allow only what is COPYed" principle above holds for grafana too, and a
# future stray file elsewhere under grafana/ is not streamed to the daemon
# (WX-278).
*
!prometheus.yml
!otel-collector-config.yml
!grafana/provisioning
!grafana/dashboards
